{
  "//": "HS-5 pre-marriage dating funnel + unplanned-pregnancy arc (docs/design/high_school_person_layer.md §9, HS-5), Sonnet 5; breakup/divorce realism pass by Fable 5 same day. Distinct from marriage_and_family_events.json's age>20 pro-career arc -- the funnel gates age < 20 (or inherits it via the hs_dating/hs_interest flag chain) and met_someone over there now gates flag_inactive hs_dating, so the two romance arcs can never collide or double-fire on the same subject. Every relationship-ending choice carries an 'end_partnership' consequence (Fable 5's ConsequenceKind.EndPartnership): the live Partner edge is RECLASSIFIED to friend/rival at an authored affinity -- never deleted, so exes stay in the graph as history and the single-partner exclusivity guard reopens for real re-dating. hs_breakup runs at realistic HS churn (weight 0.05 / cooldown 90, autopilot majority ends it -- most high-school relationships end, and now mechanically CAN). marry_hs_sweetheart is the funnel's other exit (spec §4.3 'marrying a high school sweetheart'): a year-plus hs_dating thread past age 20 converts to the married flag with the SAME Partner edge, feeding the pro file's starting_a_family/divorce arcs. Disclosed simplifications (see docs/progress.md): (1) CLOSED 2026-07-09 (Fable 5 engine pass): hs_parental_approval now gates on Family_Background.strictness >= 55 via the SubjectField extension (the poll LEFT JOINs strictness, COALESCEd to the neutral 50) -- lenient households never get the interrogation beat; safe to gate because the event sets no flags. (2) CLOSED 2026-07-09 (Sonnet 5): hs_clubhouse_cancer now graph-reaches its premise via a new SubjectField.TeammateExOfPartner (schema v13 Relationship_History -- an append-only 'ever partnered' ledger RelationshipGraph writes for free the moment any pair becomes Partner, since Relationships.type_enum only holds the CURRENT kind and a reclassified-away edge would otherwise erase the fact). The poll query answers 'does a teammate have an ex who is my current partner' from the read-only DB view (a RelPairs/HistPairs bidirectional CTE self-join), so the event only fires when the claim is real; its old random-pool 'teammate' targets are now RelationshipTargetSelector.TeammateExOfPartner, resolving the SAME teammate at apply time (live-graph WasEverPartner check) instead of a random draw, empty-pool-skips on the existing precedent. (3) hs_hometown_anchor is a one-shot flavor beat, not the doc's real weekly-minute LDR drain (needs a PhoneService/FamilyService extension); long_distance is a documented forward hook for that mechanic. (4) CLOSED 2026-07-09 (Fable 5): rekindling with an ex is now its own targeted 'rekindle_partnership' consequence (avatar-scope only) -- every end_partnership on the avatar records WHO in Game_State (avatar_ex_partner_id, in-batch), the relationship-ending choices below additionally set the hs_ex flag, and hs_rekindle re-mints the Partner edge with that specific ex (re-entering the hs_dating funnel, bitter-ex rivalry dissolving through the Phase-6 transport). The adjust-don't-reclassify rule itself is untouched -- a random 'relationship: partner' pool draw still can't re-type an existing edge, which remains what stops a feud reclassifying a marriage. keep_wondering deliberately leaves hs_ex active so the event can re-fire after its cooldown (a paced loop, not a dead-end). hs_baby_born deliberately mirrors child_is_born's shape exactly (single choice, same 270-day gestation constant) -- the only event in this batch under the 3-choice convention, matching that shipped precedent for a terminal birth beat.",
